axisymmetric/non-axisymmetric components within the sample. The two oldest\nstars in this study do show a twice as strong octupole component compared to\nthe quadrupole component. This is only seen in one out of 13 maps of the\nyounger stars. One star, chi1 Ori displays two field polarity switches during\nalmost 5 years of observations suggesting a magnetic cycle length of either 2,\n6 or 8 years.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 May 2016 14:19:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-07"}
