e disks and inner\nhalo regions of galaxies, where the abundance of Ca and Ti reflects the local\nmetal and dust content of the gas. Our study suggests that the Ti/Ca ratio\nrepresents a useful measure for the gas-to-dust ratio and overall metallicity\nin intervening absorption-line systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 May 2016 15:25:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-06"}
